  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bbf : \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel crisis: The whole country is paralyzed",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The entire country is in a state of paralysis as fuel supply activities are currently limited in the country. Traffic has been severely reduced, especially in all parts of the country.",
        "Not only in the suburbs and suburbs of the capital Colombo, but also in other cities in the country where traffic congestion is high, traffic has slowed down.",
        "The government had issued an order on the 27th to provide fuel only to the essential service units through Sibetco filling stations.",
        "Accordingly, the government has decided to supply fuel only to the Health Services, Public Transport, Railways and the 3rd Battalion.",
        "Many intellectuals are of the opinion that this decision will cause great inconvenience to those who rely on the private transport sector for their daily commute and services.",
        "They say that the country is on the verge of paralysis due to lack of fuel and that food, clothing and shelter are the only things that can sustain human life. However, now this has changed.",
        "Intellectuals point out that many of our countrymen are now forced to wander around like nomads, without food, without change of clothes, and unable to sleep at home.",
        "The government's decision to distribute fuel only to the essential services due to fuel shortages in the country has hit the transport sector hard, with bus drivers and operators in the transport sector, tricycle drivers, food and package distributors on motorcycles and taxi drivers facing a major economic crisis.",
        "In this case, the I.O.C. Fuel is being distributed at petrol stations in limited quantities according to the type of vehicles. Accordingly, the IOC has decided to provide petrol for motorcycles at Rs. 1500, three wheelers at Rs. 2500 and motor vehicles at Rs. 7000. Has taken action.",
        "Nevertheless, the general public has been waiting in long queues to get tokens to get petrol.",
        "The order issued by the government to provide fuel only to the essential service units will be in force till July 10th.",
        "However, they feared that the country would face dire consequences if the order was continued.",
        "Therefore, the government must take decisive action as soon as possible to ensure that the people have access to essential commodities, including fuel and gas, without hindrance.",
        "Moreover, intellectuals say that political leaders need to make meaningful decisions in order to make political decisions to take the country on the path of development."
      ],
